    "unlock": "engineer",
    "blurb": "Four corner beacons in a fog-drowned moonlit vale. The dark hides what comes; keep one light burning to dawn and rove between the corners to relight what falls.",
    "newFeatures": [
      "BEACON DEFENSE: four corner lights, keep one burning",
      "NIGHT VEIL: darkness shrinks enemy sight — brazier pools matter",
      "PHASEBORN drift through the ruin walls; FROSTSHADES chill in the gloom"
    ]
  },
  "ambience": "meadow",
  "intro": [
    {
      "title": "The Four Lights",
      "lines": [
        "Four beacon monoliths anchor the corners of this fog-drowned vale, and the waves split between every light still burning.",
        "Out here the dark is a wall — the enemy can't see far, and neither can you past the brazier pools. Phaseborn slip the ruin stones; frostshades chill where they touch.",
        "A beacon beaten to nothing goes DARK, not dead: stand at it by day, hold ACT, pay 8 shards — it burns again. Lose only if all four go dark at once."
      ],
      "art": "siege"
    }
  ],
  "outro": [
    {
      "title": "Lights Over the Vale",
      "lines": [
        "However it ended, the vale kept a light burning against the dark.",
        "Four monoliths hum behind you in the lifting fog. The frontier maps call it holdable now."
      ],
      "art": "dawn"
    }
  ],
